Phase 1: Planning & Research

Define core features (sales, inventory, customer management).

Pick your tech stack (backend, frontend, database).

Map out data flow: how sales and inventory connect.

Phase 2: Build Your MVP

Develop basic sales entry and dashboard.

Implement simple inventory tracking.

Manually link sales to inventory usage at first.

Phase 3: Testing & Feedback

Test the MVP in your own restaurant.

Collect feedback from staff or trusted customers.

Phase 4: Automation & Refinement

Automate inventory deduction when an order is placed.

Add notifications for low stock and reordering.

Phase 5: Scalability & Outsourcing

Refine code and database for multiple clients.

Document everything—user guides, onboarding processes.

Begin offering your solution to other restaurants.

======================================================
PHASE-1:
Features:
1️⃣ Customer Order System (Front-End)
-------------------------------------

A screen where customer orders are entered (by staff / POS).

Items selected from menu (example: white rice, dal, curry).

Quantity selection.

Order confirmation.


2️⃣ Kitchen Order Ticket (KOT) System
----------------------------------------

Once an order is placed:

It should instantly appear on the kitchen dashboard.

Display:

Order ID

Items

Quantity

Time

Option to:

Print kitchen ticket

Mark order as “Prepared / Done”


3️⃣ Customer Receipt / Bill Printing
------------------------------------

Generate customer receipt automatically.

Should include:

Items

Quantity

Price

Total

Date & time

Printable (normal POS printer / browser print).


4️⃣ Automatic Inventory Deduction
--------------------------------

Each menu item is linked to ingredients.

Example:

White Rice → Rice (raw) X grams

When customer orders:

Inventory automatically reduces.

Happens in real time, no manual update.



5️⃣ Inventory Management Dashboard
--------------------------------

You want to see:

Current stock available

Item-wise consumption

What is low stock

What to purchase next

Purchase suggestions:

Daily

Weekly

Visibility like:

“You need to buy 10 kg rice by tomorrow”


6️⃣ Sales Analytics & Reports (Backend Dashboard)
------------------------------------------------

You want item-wise and time-wise sales, including:

📊 Time-Based Reports

Daily sales

Weekly sales

Monthly sales

Quarterly sales

Yearly sales

🍽️ Item-Based Reports

Item-wise sales (e.g., White Rice sold = 120 plates)

Revenue per item

Best-selling items

Least-selling items


7️⃣ Business Owner Dashboard
----------------------------

One place where you can see:

Total sales today

Orders completed / pending

Inventory status

Purchase suggestions

Performance overview


8️⃣ Future Vision (Implicit but Important)
--------------------------------------------

You want to:

Use it for your own restaurant

Sell / outsource it to other restaurants

So system must be:

Scalable

Multi-restaurant ready (later phase)


***TECHNOLOGY***
------------------
Backend: Node.js (with Express). It’s fast, great for real-time apps, and has a rich ecosystem.

Frontend: React. It’s flexible, component-based, and perfect for dynamic dashboards (sales, kitchen tickets).

Database: MongoDB (if you prefer NoSQL, flexible for evolving needs) or PostgreSQL (if you want relational data structure).

For real-time order updates (like kitchen tickets), use WebSockets (via Socket.io) to push live updates to the kitchen and dashboards.


***🗂️ DATA FLOW***
----------------------
Customer Order
      ↓
Backend Server
      ↓
Kitchen Dashboard (Live)
      ↓
Order Completed
      ↓
Inventory Deducted
      ↓
Sales Stored
      ↓
Reports + Purchase Suggestions

